Those on the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span>'s left wing who had quietly opposed Dingeldey's turn to the right have now resigned en masse. Hans Bechly, Frank Glatzel, and Otto Thiel—prominent figures within the white-collar DHV union—have also stepped down, with Bechly being the longtime chairman of the association.

With their exodus, the party’s last remaining link to the German white-collar movement has been severed, along with a significant portion of its electoral base. The only consolation Dingeldey can claim is that the party’s loss in seats will be somewhat mitigated by its electoral connection to the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>.